post_text:
Did you know that Suicide Prevention Month and Recovery Month are both observed in September?

The challenges we have experienced so far in 2020 have tested our resiliency and at times dampened our hope. However, throughout difficult times, we have also seen that when we work together, we are more powerful than when we act alone. Now more than ever we need inspiration and a clear vision of hope, recovery and resiliency to unite us and move us forward.

Visit www.eachmindmatters.org/SPW2020/ for resources and activities to support you this September.

post_text:
Calling all Students, families and school staff,

Tuesday August 17th was the first day of LACOE's countywide "CHALK-A-THON'', which runs from August 17th to September 7, and invites students, families and school staff to create sidewalk art promoting 2020 Census participation.

Participants who share their artwork on social media (using hashtags #CaStudentsCount, #LACcensuschalkathon and your school site) will have a chance to win giveaway!

All art pieces should include "2020census.gov" and "Everyone Counts" messages. Multiple languages are encouraged!
